
[1]betake

   BETA'KE, v.t. pret. betook; pp. betaken. [be and take.]

   1. To take to; to have recourse to; to apply; to resort; with the
   reciprocal pronoun; as, to betake ourselves to arms, or to action. It
   generally implies a motion towards an object, as to betake ourselves to
   a shade grove; or an application of the mind or faculties,
   corresponding with such motion, as to betake ourselves to study or to
   vice.

   2. Formerly, to take or seize.
